te%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20ALS%20community%2C%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Jack%20Dunn%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20have%20the%20best%20talks%20with%20my%20preteen%20son%20when%20I%20drive%20him%20to%20school%20in%20the%20morning.%20I%20hope%20he%20knows%20I'm%20always%20here%20for%20him.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222630%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20with%20her%20son%2C%20both%20wearing%20Gator's%20Basketball%20merch.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693ad3947ecd1d1da6635a36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222390%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20tries%20to%20make%20sure%20her%20son's%20birthday%20feels%20separate%20from%20holiday%20celebrations.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ashley%20Archambault%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20son%20became%20quieter%20as%20he%20entered%20his%20tween%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECar%20rides%20turned%20into%20our%20most%20meaningful%20time%20together.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShowing%20up%20consistently%20matters%20more%20than%20forcing%20conversations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20son%20was%20still%20under%205%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fill-never-go-back-to-booktok-after-getting-library-card-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elocal%20library%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20my%20free%20time%2C%20my%20son%20was%20basically%20my%20best%20buddy.%20My%20supervisor%20at%20the%20time%20had%20teenagers%2C%20so%20she%20was%20in%20a%20different%20parenting%20stage%20than%20I%20was.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20her%20saying%20that%20the%20secret%20to%20keeping%20her%20kids%20close%20was%20to%20drive%20them%20around%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%20This%20kept%20her%20kids%20talking%20to%20her%20and%20enabled%20her%20to%20maintain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-popular-in-high-school-isnt-as-good-for-you-as-having-a-few-close-friends-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eclose%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20so%20right%20with%20her%20advice.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2246db6704-98d1-441e-a346-2e91bfc080ae%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20son%20is%20now%20a%20tween%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20just%20turned%2012%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstill-caring-for-adult-children-learning-to-let-them-go-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshift%20from%20boy%20to%20teenager%3C%2Fa%3E%20seems%20to%20have%20happened%20overnight.%20He%20is%20becoming%20more%20independent%20and%20less%20talkative%20%E2%80%94%20with%20me%2C%20but%20not%20his%20social%20circle.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20it's%20the%20natural%20order%20of%20things%20for%20him%20to%20spread%20his%20wings%20and%20to%20push%20back%20a%20bit%20against%20me.%20But%20sometimes%20I%20just%20really%20miss%20my%20best%20buddy%20and%20all%20the%20fun%20we%20had%20spending%20time%20together%20when%20he%20was%20little.%20Now%2C%20when%20he's%20home%20from%20school%2C%20he's%20often%20in%20his%20room%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-a-landline-helped-my-kids-make-their-own-plans-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etalking%20on%20the%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20his%20friends%20or%20playing%20games%20online%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20my%20former%20boss's%20wisdom%20stuck%20with%20me%2C%20because%20the%20idea%20of%20my%20son%20growing%20up%20and%20not%20wanting%20to%20talk%20to%20me%20scared%20me.%20I've%20come%20to%20realize%20that%20driving%20my%20son%20around%20whenever%20I%20get%20the%20chance%20is%20basically%20priceless.%20Right%20now%2C%20drives%20with%20him%20are%20primarily%20to%20and%20from%20school%2C%20but%20during%20football%20or%20basketball%20seasons%2C%20all%20of%20the%20practices%20and%20games%20really%20add%20up.%20This%20year%2C%20sixth%20grade%20has%20really%20felt%20like%20a%20turning%20point%2C%20because%20I've%20noticed%20an%20increase%20in%20invites%20to%20parties%2C%20hangouts%2C%20and%20sleepovers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realize%20that%20as%20he%20gets%20older%2C%20these%20social%20outings%20will%20only%20increase.%20And%20then%20one%20day%2C%20when%20he's%20closer%20to%20age%2016%2C%20he'll%20likely%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearn-extra-money-with-these-21-high-paying-side-jobs-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epart-time%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20add%20to%20his%20schedule.%20As%20long%20as%20he%20doesn't%20have%20a%20car%2C%20I%20know%20I'll%20be%20his%20main%20source%20of%20transportation.%20Instead%20of%20dreading%2C%20I%20know%20these%20are%20actually%20the%20hidden%20opportunities%2C%20like%20diamonds%20in%20the%20rough%2C%20to%20remain%20connected%20to%20him%20as%20he%20grows%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fa7f1662-5dbf-403a-881e-a5270c3bcfc9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20best%20to%20allow%20our%20conversations%20to%20flow%20naturally%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20try%20to%20force%20a%20topic%20on%20him%2C%20because%20I%20have%20found%20that%20it's%20not%20the%20best%20timing%20for%20discipline-based%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskip-small-talk-have-deep-conversations-2016-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eserious%20talks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'm%20sure%20he%20feels%20trapped%2C%20so%20he%20shuts%20down%2C%20and%20it%20ruins%20the%20safe%20space%20I'm%20trying%20to%20develop%20out%20of%20our%20car%20rides.%20Allowing%20the%20conversation%20to%20flow%20organically%20is%20when%20he'll%20surprise%20me%20and%20ask%20me%20something%20random%20or%20open%20up%20about%20something%20that's%20been%20bothering%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20he%20doesn't%20open%20up%20every%20time%2C%20I%20know%20I'm%20giving%20him%20the%20space%20to%20do%20so.%20Often%2C%20after%20a%20few%20minutes%20of%20being%20stuck%20in%20the%20car%20together%2C%20one%20of%20us%20will%20start%20talking%20about%20something.%20I%20think%20having%20the%20music%20on%20and%20sightseeing%20on%20our%20way%20everywhere%20gives%20our%20brains%20distractions%20and%20talking%20points.%20It%20feels%20like%20the%20car%20is%20sometimes%20the%20white%20flag%20zone%2C%20where%20we%20stop%20arguing%20and%20start%20talking%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he's%20mostly%20reserved%2C%20there%20are%20other%20times%20when%20he's%20more%20open%20and%20chatty%2C%20and%20I%20just%20let%20him%20vent%20and%20do%20my%20best%20to%20listen.%20It's%20likely%20therapeutic%20to%20have%20someone%20who%20will%20just%20listen%20to%20him%20at%20his%20age%2C%20but%20it%20might%20also%20be%20easier%20for%20him%20to%20open%20up%20to%20me%20side-by-side%20instead%20of%20face-to-face.%20Knowing%20there's%20an%20endpoint%2C%20such%20as%20knowing%20we'll%20be%20at%20his%20school%20in%20five%20minutes%2C%20likely%20helps%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b7e55207-b88a-4cf8-a2d0-2373a3fe54ff%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20hope%20I'm%20also%20sending%20him%20the%20message%20that%20I%20won't%20stop%20showing%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWillingly%20taking%20him%20everywhere%20he%20needs%20to%20go%20daily%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20communicating%20to%20him%20that%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20stop%20showing%20up%20for%20him.%20That%20no%20matter%20how%20tense%20things%20may%20be%20at%20times%20between%20us%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20there%20for%20all%20of%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20it%20reassures%20him%20that%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20give%20up%20on%20my%20job%20as%20his%20mom%2C%20even%20when%20things%20get%20tough.%20I'll%20be%20sitting%20there%20in%20silence%20if%20that's%20what%20he%20needs%2C%20but%20the%20message%20I%20hope%20to%20send%20him%20is%3A%20I'm%20still%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20o