0Air%20and%20Space%20Museum's%20second%2C%20larger%20location%20in%20Virginia.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20exhibit%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20controversy%20as%20interest%20groups%20have%20debated%20the%20plane's%20legacy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Enola%20Gay%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwwii-planes-atomic-bomb-b-29-bockscar-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBoeing%20B-29%20Superfortress%20bomber%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20dropped%20the%20atomic%20bomb%20on%20Hiroshima%20in%20World%20War%20II%2C%20is%20so%20large%20that%20it%20couldn't%20fit%20into%20the%20Smithsonian%20National%20Air%20and%20Space%20Museum's%20flagship%20location%20on%20the%20National%20Mall%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20it's%20displayed%20at%20the%20museum's%20second%20location%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-and-space-museum-attractions-exhibits-planes-restoration-hangar-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESteven%20F.%20Udvar-Hazy%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Chantilly%2C%20Virginia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Udvar-Hazy%20Center%20features%20over%20200%20aircraft%20on%20display%2C%20but%20the%20Enola%20Gay%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20objects%20in%20its%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20historic%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEnola%20Gay%20dropped%20the%20first-ever%20atomic%20bomb%20used%20in%20warfare%20on%20Hiroshima%20on%20August%206%2C%201945.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Enola%20Gay%20airplane.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6977ce8ae1ba468a96aab8b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22657%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEnola%20Gay.%3Cp%3EPhoto%2012%2FAnn%20Ronan%20Picture%20Library%2FPhoto%2012%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20second%20%26quot%3BFat%20Man%26quot%3B%20atomic%20bomb%20was%20dropped%20on%20Nagasaki%20on%20August%209%2C%201945%2C%20by%20another%20Boeing%20B-29%20Superfortress%20named%20Bockscar%2C%20which%20is%20on%20display%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-force-museum-planes-missiles-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENational%20Museum%20of%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Dayton%2C%20Ohio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emperor%20of%20Japan%20announced%20the%20country's%20surrender%20on%20August%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20plane%20was%20named%20after%20pilot%20Paul%20Tibbets'%20mother%2C%20Enola%20Gay%20Tibbets.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20crew%20of%20the%20Enola%20Gay.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6977ce04e1ba468a96aab89f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUNITED%20STATES%20-%20APRIL%2006%3A%20Crew%20of%20the%20Enola%20Gay%2C%20the%20infamous%20B-29%20plane%20from%20which%20the%20first%20atom%20bomb%20was%20dropped.%20(Left%20to%20right)%20Major%20Thomas%20W.%20Ferebee%2C%20Col.%20Paul%20W.%20Tibbetts%20Jr.%2C%20Major%20Theodore%20J.%20Van%20Kirk%2C%20Capt.%20Kermit%20Beahan%2C%20Capt.%20Robert%20Lewis%2C%20Sergt.%20Wyatt%20E.%20Duzenbury%20and%20Sergt.%20George%20Caron.%3Cp%3EArt%20Edger%2FNY%20Daily%20News%20Archive%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETibbets%20commanded%20the%20Air%20Force's%20509th%20Composite%20Group%20in%20charge%20of%20deploying%20nuclear%20weapons.%20The%20hand-picked%20squadron%20trained%20at%20an%20abandoned%20airfield%20in%20Windover%2C%20Utah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20%26quot%3BLittle%20Boy%26quot%3B%20atomic%20bomb%20deployed%20by%20the%20Enola%20Gay%20weighed%209%2C700%20pounds.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20%26quot%3BLittle%20Boy%26quot%3B%20atomic%20bomb%20while%20it%20was%20loaded%20into%20the%20Enola%20Gay.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6977ceb4e1ba468a96aab8b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EView%20of%20the%20atomic%20bomb%2C%20codenamed%20'Little%20Boy%2C'%20as%20it%20is%20hoisted%20into%20the%20bomb%20bay%20of%20the%20B-29%20Superfortress%20'Enola%20Gay'%20on%20the%20North%20Field%20of%20Tinian%20airbase%2C%20North%20Marianas%20Islands%2C%20early%20August%2C%201945.%20The%20bomb%20was%20dropped%20on%20the%20Japanese%20city%20of%20Hiroshima%20on%20August%206.%3Cp%3EPhotoQuest%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20the%20B-29%20aircraft%20capable%20of%20carrying%20the%20atomic%20bomb%2C%20all%20of%20its%20protective%20and%20defensive%20armament%2C%20except%20for%20the%2050-caliber%20tailguns%2C%20were%20removed%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20excess%20weight.%20It%20was%20also%20left%20unpainted%2C%20which%20saved%20the%20850%20pounds%20that%20the%20paint%20would%20have%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20bomb%20exploded%201%2C900%20feet%20above%20Hiroshima%20with%20devastating%20effects.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hiroshima%20after%20the%20atomic%20bomb.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6977cf0ca645d11881880122%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221133%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHiroshima%20after%20the%20atomic%20explosion%20of%20August%201945.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2070%2C000%20people%20died%20in%20the%20initial%20blast%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-hiroshima-timeline-bombing-wwii-manhattan-project-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebombing%20of%20Hiroshima%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20death%20toll%20over%20five%20years%20may%20have%20exceeded%20200%2C000%20people%20due%20to%20the%20