et%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69986ccba645d1188189a934%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22702%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20FBI%20released%20this%20image%20related%20to%20the%20disappearance%20of%20Nancy%20Guthrie.%3Cp%3EFBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20only%20item%20that%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bpositively%20identified%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20suspect%20in%20the%20doorbell%20camera%20footage%20is%20the%20Ozark%20Trail%20Hiker%20packpack%2C%20a%20Pima%20County%20Sheriff's%20Department%20spokeswoman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvestigators%20are%20working%20to%20determine%20where%20the%20other%20items%20may%20have%20been%20purchased%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokeswoman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENancy%20Guthrie's%20disappearance%20has%20gripped%20the%20nation.%20Her%20famous%20daughter%2C%20Savannah%20Guthrie%2C%20has%20issued%20tearful%20video%20messages%2C%20pleading%20for%20her%20mother's%20safe%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAuthorities%20have%20not%20publicly%20identified%20any%20suspects%20or%20persons%20of%20interest%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDNA%20found%20at%20Nancy%20Guthrie's%20property%20is%20being%20analyzed%20by%20investigators%2C%20the%20sheriff's%20department%20said%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20Nanos%2C%20the%20sheriff%2C%20said%20the%20Guthrie%20family%2C%20including%20all%20siblings%20and%20spouses%2C%20has%20been%20cleared%20as%20possible%20suspects%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20family%20has%20been%20nothing%20but%20cooperative%20and%20gracious%20and%20are%20victims%20in%20this%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Nanos%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-google-nancy-guthrie-disappearance-police-fbi-video-footage-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771677956000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69976cd2e1ba468a96ac56ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-google-nancy-guthrie-disappearance-police-fbi-video-footage-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Google%20and%20Walmart%20have%20both%20emerged%20as%20significant%20players%20in%20the%20law%20enforcement%20investigation%20into%20the%20disappearance%20of%20Savannah%20Guthrie's%20mother.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nmusumeci%40businessinsider.com%20(Natalie%20Musumeci)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-google-nancy-guthrie-disappearance-police-fbi-video-footage-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Army's%20new%20drone%20competition%20is%20really%20a%20talent%20hunt.%20It's%20scouting%20out%20what%20makes%20a%20top%20drone%20pilot.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20soldier%20sits%20on%20the%20ground%20wearing%20a%20headset%20and%20holding%20a%20controller.%20Behind%20him%2C%20various%20soldiers%20crouch%2C%20sit%2C%20and%20stand.%20There%20is%20a%20barren%20tree%20line%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69987b432237a6a8f0cd866e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20Army%20held%20its%20first%20annual%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%20in%20Huntsville%2C%20Alabama%2C%20bringing%20operators%20from%20across%20the%20service%20to%20compete%20in%20two%20lanes.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Sgt.%20Aaron%20Troutman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Army%20is%20evaluating%20what%20types%20of%20criteria%2C%20like%20being%20a%20gamer%2C%20make%20the%20best%20drone%20pilots.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20service%20held%20its%20first%20annual%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%2C%20bringing%20together%20operators%20from%20across%20the%20service.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EArmy%20officials%20said%20the%20event%20helped%20them%20continue%20to%20evaluate%20training%20needs%20for%20drone%20pilots.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Army%20used%20its%20first%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%20not%20just%20to%20test%20skills%2C%20officials%20say%2C%20but%20to%20identify%20what%20makes%20a%20top%20drone%20operator%20%E2%80%94%20and%20who%20in%20the%20force%20is%20best%20suited%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20training%20every%20soldier%20to%20fly%20drones%2C%20the%20Army%20is%20using%20competition%20to%20identify%20the%20skill%20sets%20of%20top%20drone%20operators%20and%20whether%20there%20are%20specific%20roles%20within%20units%20that%20would%20make%20the%20most%20sense%20for%20working%20with%20uncrewed%20aerial%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20effort%20reflects%20a%20broader%20shift%20from%20treating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-learning-drone-lessons-bad-signals-broken-parts-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edrone%20flying%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20something%20for%20all%20soldiers%20to%20approaching%20it%20as%20a%20specialized%20skill%20set%20that%20requires%20the%20right%20aptitude%2C%20training%2C%20and%20sustained%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inaugural%20drone%20competition%20took%20place%20this%20week%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alabama%20in%20Huntsville%2C%20gathering%20teams%20from%20across%20active%2C%20Reserve%2C%20and%20National%20Guard%20units.%20There%20were%20no%20requirements%20on%20what%20types%20of%20soldiers%20could%20participate%20or%20where%20they%20came%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20just%20send%20your%20best%20UAS%20operators%2C%26quot%3B%20Col.%20Nicholas%20Ryan%2C%20director%20of%20Army%20UAS%20Transformation%20at%20the%20Aviation%20Center%20of%20Excellence%2C%20told%20reporters%2C%20prompting%20a%20mix%20of%20operators%20with%20different%20backgrounds%20and%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20three%20days%2C%20soldiers%20competed%20in%20multiple%20events%2C%20testing%20their%20piloting%20skills.%20The%20first%20was%20an%20obstacle%20course%20that%20operators%20navigated%20using%20first-person-view%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20soldier%20holds%20a%20drone%20controller.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69987c0b156648bc16a89591%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERecent%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20directives%20have%20prioritized%20the%20development%20and%20integration%20of%20drones%20across%20the%20Army.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Spc.%20Michelle%20Lessard-Terry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20was%20a%20hunter-killer%20scenario%20in%20which%20teams%20used%20a%20reconnaissance%20drone%20to%20survey%20an%20array%20of%20targets%20and%20decide%20which%20were%20highest%20priority%20for%20simulated%20strikes%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-new-cheap-one-way-attack-drone-force-middle-east-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eone-way%20attack%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20competition%20didn't%20involve%20any%20kinetic%20strikes%3B%20instead%2C%20soldiers%20flew%20the%20drones%20into%20nets%20on%20the%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20event%20was%20focused%20on%20innovation.%20Soldiers%20could%20build%2C%20modify%2C%20and%20test%20their%20own%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20said%20that%20the%20Army%20was%20taking%20notes%20throughout%20the%20competition%20on%20who%20the%20top%20operators%20were%2C%20calling%20it%20talent%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20not%20about%20receiving%20trophies%20or%20awards%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20is%20about%20identifying%20what%20sets%20the%20top%20drone%20operators%20apart%20and%20figuring%20out%20how%20they%20developed%20those%20skills.%20The%20goal%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20to%20understand%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20lessons%20can%20we%20take%20from%20this%20to%20find%20out%20who%20the%20best%20operator%20is%20and%20how%20they%20became%20the%20best%20operator.%20What%20skills%20and%20resources%20and%20training%20allowed%20them%20to%20become%20the%20best%20operator%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoldiers%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Ukraine%20have%20noticed%20that%20gamers%20make%20excellent%20drone%20pilots%2C%20as%20do%20soldiers%20who%20have%20experience%20piloting%20hobby%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20something%20we're%20absolutely%20looking%20at%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArmy%20leaders%20have%20previously%20noted%20a%20correlation%20between%20soldiers%20who%20grew%20up%20playing%20video%20games%20%E2%80%94%20or%20who%20are%20active%20gamers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20drone%20proficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETroops%20who%20game%20have%20shown%20quick%20reflexes%2C%20precise%20hand-eye%20coordination%2C%20and%20strong%20spatial%20awareness%20that%20make%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-captain-says-top-drone-pilots-are-video-gamers-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompetent%20with%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20an%20exercise%20in%20Germany%20last%20fall%2C%20a%20US%20Army%20captain%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20top%20pilots%20were%20soldiers%20who%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20they%20got%20off%20on%20Fridays%2C%20then%20go%20and%20play%20video%20games.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20has%20been%20restructuring%20its%20approach%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-taps-companies-ukrainian-for-attack-drones-competition-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edrone%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rewriting%20its%20training%20and%20focusing%20on%20integrating%20soldiers%20with%20small%20drone%20training%20into%20front-line%20units.%20Lessons%20and%20approaches%20are%20being%20shared%20across%20the%20service%2C%20building%20a%20broader%20doctrine%20on%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-mastering-drone-warfare-doesnt-mean-always-right-weapon-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EArmy%20is%20adopting%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20quadcopter%20drone%20flies%20on%20a%20field%20with%20trees%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69987c93efb52c8bd0de8bf2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225147%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20competition%20allowed%20Army%20leadership%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20skillsets%20and%20backgrounds%20that%20make%20drone%20operators%20successful.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Sgt.%20Aaron%20Troutman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20said%20that%20the%20service%20is%20realizing%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-every-us-army-soldier-needs-a-drone-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eflying%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20dedicated%20assignment.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20be%20a%20squad%20rifleman%20and%20a%20drone%20operator%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20one%20or%20the%20other%20because%20you%20have%20to%20have%20the%20level%20of%20skill%20and%20expertise%20in%20operating%20and%20employing%20the%20drones.%20That's%20what%20you%20have%20to%20be%20good%20at%20and%20train%20at%20and%20focus%20on%20for%20most%20of%20your%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Army%20officials%20said%20efforts%20like%20the%20competition%20were%20demonstrating%20where%20drones%20best%20fit%20in%20a%20formation%20and%20what%20aspects%20of%20training%20are%20most%20important%20to%20maintain%20these%20highly%20perishable%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20soldiers%20flew%20their%20drones%20successfully%2C%20but%20the%20Army%20did%20take%20note%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-drone-wins-hint-at-how-behind-it-is-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecommunication%20breakdowns%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20soldiers%20went%20through%20the%20hunter-killer%20lane%2C%20specifically%20getting%20drones%20into%20position%20and%20identifying%20and%20simulating%20strikes%20on%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20an%20example%20of%20something%20we%20didn't%20anticipate%2C%20but%20it's%20absolutely%20standing%20out%20as%20that%20is%20something%20we%20as%20an%20Army%20need%20to%20do%20better%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20going%20to%20proliferate%20these%20drones%20and%20want%20them%20to%20be%20more%20effective%20and%20lethal%2C%20we%20just%20need%20to%20improve%20on%20how%20our%20soldiers%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20to%20communicate%20when%20they're%20using%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20future%20iterations%20of%20the%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%2C%20the%20Army%20hopes%20to%20include%20kinetic%20elements%20as%20well%20as%20electronic%20warfare%20and%20jamming%20to%20better%20replicate%20real-world%20scenarios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-all-army-soldiers-can-fly-drones-scouting-talent-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771677901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69987df4efb52c8bd0de8c2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-all-army-soldiers-can-fly-drones-scouting-talent-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Army's%20first%20annual%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%20shed%20some%20new%20light%20on%20the%20ideal%20backgrounds%20and%20skill%20sets%20for%20drone%20pilots.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-all-army-soldiers-can-fly-drones-scouting-talent-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Thousands%20of%20military%20families%20are%20stuck%20on%20childcare%20waitlists.%20More%20spots%20may%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20fix%20the%20deeper%20problems.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224826%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Force%20childcare%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998ab94156648bc16a89cb6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223217%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20military%20childcare%20development%20centers%20support%20service%20members%20and%20their%20families.%20There%20are%2C%20however%2C%20thousands%20of%20children%20waiting%20for%20spots%20to%20open%20up.%3Cp%3EAirman%20Paden%20Henry%2FUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAround%207%2C800%20military%20children%20are%20waitlisted%20for%20childcare%2C%20according%20to%20congressional%20estimates.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAdvocates%20say%20the%20real%20number%20may%20be%20higher.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStaff%20shortages%20and%20high%20attrition%20are%20persistent%20problems%20for%20military%20childcare%20facilities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20an%20estimated%207%2C800%20children%20on%20US%20military%20childcare%20waitlists.%20Military%20families%20and%20advocates%20say%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20number%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emasks%20deeper%20shortfalls%20that%20continue%20to%20sideline%20working%20spouses%20and%20strain%20service%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawmakers%20raised%20the%20issue%20during%20a%20recent%20congressional%20hearing%2C%20calling%20the%20persistent%20backlog%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawmakers-push-to-prevent-barracks-funds-from-supporting-domestic-operations-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equality-of-life%3C%2Fa%3E%20problem%2C%20even%20as%20the%20waitlist%20has%20notably%20dropped%20from%2012%2C000%20children%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20number%20isn't%20the%20whole%20picture%20and%20excludes%20families%20who've%20given%20up%20out%20of%20frustration%20or%20can't%20use%20base%20centers%20that%20lack%20evening%2C%20weekend%2C%20or%20specialized%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20say%20that%20we%20are%20a%20military%20that%20cares%20about%20our%20families%20if%20we%20pretend%20to%20provide%20childcare%20and%20then%20we've%20got%20a%20waitlist%20that's%20got%207%2C800%20babies%20waiting%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Massachusetts%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20said%20to%20service%20senior%20enlisted%20leaders%20during%20last%20week's%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20service%20leaders%20present%20disputed%20that%20figure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaster%20Chief%20Petty%20Officer%20of%20the%20Navy%20John%20Perryman%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20Navy%20still%20has%20roughly%201%2C400%20children%20in%20unmet%20need%20status%2C%20while%20Chief%20Master%20Sergeant%20of%20the%20Air%20Force%20David%20Wolfe%20said%20his%20service's%20waitlist%20stands%20at%20around%202%2C700%2C%20though%20there%20are%20efforts%20underway%20to%20open%20new%20spots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20clear%20how%20the%20remaining%20waitlisted%20children%20are%20divided%20between%20other%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20Air%20Force%20had%2095%2C000%20children%20under%205%20but%20space%20for%20only%20about%2023%2C000%20in%20its%20child%20development%20centers%2C%20a%202023%20service%20report%20on%20childcare%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Air%20Force%20spokesperson%20attributed%20that%20disparity%20to%20the%20number%20of%20children%20entering%20and%20leaving%20care%20throughout%20the%20year.%20%26quot%3BThe%20annual%20number%20served%20will%20not%20correlate%20with%20daily%20capacity%20and%20can%20be%20significantly%20higher%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20families%20require%20on-base%20care.%20But%20the%20report%20added%20that%20more%20facility%20construction%20alone%20would%20not%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bviable%20solution%20to%20meet%20all%20potential%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKayla%20Corbitt%2C%20a%20military%20spouse%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20a%20nonprofit%20dedicated%20to%20helping%20military%20families%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-family-spent-savings-on-expensive-childcare-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efind%20reliable%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20many%20families%20lose%20hope%20amid%20long%20waits.%20Staying%20on%20the%20waitlist%2C%20she%20said%2C%20requires%20logging%20on%20every%20couple%20of%20months%20to%20reconfirm%20before%20families%20are%20automatically%20disenrolled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20some%20families%2C%20the%20barriers%20extend%20beyond%20backlogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223808%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20room%20at%20the%20CDC%20at%20Ramstein%20Air%20Base%2C%20Germany%2C%20Jan.%2014%2C%202026.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998ac4f2237a6a8f0cd8df0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222539%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20room%20at%20the%20CDC%20at%20Ramstein%20Air%20Base%2C%20Germany%2C%20Jan.%2014%2C%202026.%3Cp%3EAirman%20Paden%20Henry%2FUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnyone%20needing%20evening%20care%2C%20weekend%20care%2C%20shift%20work%20care%2C%20which%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20military%2C%20they%20aren't%20going%20to%20try%20to%20get%20on%20that%20waitlist%2C%26quot%3B%20Corbitt%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20most%20child%20development%20centers%2C%20or%20CDCs%2C%20on%20bases%20don't%20offer%20late%20evening%20or%20very%20early%20morning%20care%20needed%20for%20troops%20on%2024-hour%20duty%20or%20for%20deployed%20service%20members%20with%20spouses%20who%20work%20unusual%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20children%20with%20special%20needs%20face%20significant%20obstacles%20in%20finding%20care%2C%20Corbitt%20said%2C%20as%20many%20CDCs%20are%20not%20equipped%20to%20provide%20care%2C%20and%20the%20policies%20sometimes%20vary%20from%20facility%20to%20facility%2C%20making%20it%20hard%20for%20families%20to%20know%20what%20to%20expect%20when%20they%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrigit%20Schneider%2C%20an%20Air%20Force%20spouse%20and%20mother%20of%20three%20children%2C%20wants%20to%20return%20to%20work%20as%20a%20financial%20planner%20to%20better%20support%20her%20family%2C%20but%20because%20her%20local%20childcare%20center%20won't%20accept%20children%20with%20feeding%20tubes%2C%20one%20of%20her%20young%20children%20is%20shut%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20special%20needs%20mom%20perspective%2C%20it's%20an%20extra%20layer%20of%20challenge%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchneider%20pays%20nearly%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20one%20child%20to%20receive%20on-base%20childcare%2C%20another%20child%20is%20receiving%20private%20care%20due%20to%20the%20severity%20of%20their%20disability%2C%20and%20a%20third%20is%20at%20home.%20Schneider%20says%20the%20third%20should%20be%20able%20to%20receive%20base%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20G-tube%20really%20is%20not%20a%20hard%20medical%20device%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20though%2C%20military%20CDCs%20won't%20accept%20children%20with%20gastrostomy%20tubes.%20Facilities%20are%20often%20unable%2C%20or%20unwilling%2C%20to%20provide%20higher%20levels%20of%20care%2C%20Corbitt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20Force%20childcare%20programs%20are%20%26quot%3Bsupported%20by%20a%20multidisciplinary%20team%20of%20experts%20who%20provide%20consultation%20and%20support%20to%20ensure%20the%20highest%20quality%20of%20inclusive%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Air%20Force%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20following%20a%20query%20regarding%20the%20service's%20childcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20service%20%26quot%3Boffers%20a%20network%20of%20on-%20and%20off-installation%20care%20options%20and%20works%20closely%20with%20families%20to%20identify%20the%20appropriate%20setting%20for%20their%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20spokesperson%2C%20adding%20that%20waitlist%20data%20helps%20inform%20future%20allocation%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaffing%20shortages%20are%20another%20obstacle%20to%20reliable%20access%20for%20military%20personnel.%20Military%20childcare%20workers%20face%20unusually%20high%20attrition%20rates%2C%20around%2050%25%2C%20Warren%20said%20at%20last%20week's%20congressional%20hearing%2C%20driven%20largely%20by%20meager%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompounding%20the%20issue%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20clear%20pathway%20that%20would%20allow%20qualified%20providers%20to%20move%20easily%20between%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%2040%25%20of%20childcare%20workers%20are%20military%20spouses%2C%20said%20the%20Marine%20Corps'%20top%20enlisted%20leader%2C%20Sergeant%20Major%20Carlos%20Ruiz%2C%20during%20the%20hearing.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20just%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20smart%20about%20transferring%20folks%20and%20directly%20hiring%20from%20one%20CDC%20to%20another%2C%20we%20can%20reduce%20the%20attrition%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20watchdogs%20have%20repeatedly%20flagged%20childcare%20accessibility%20as%20a%20point%20of%20concern%20for%20the%20US%20military.%20A%202024%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20report%20found%20that%20while%20the%20services%20focus%20heavily%20on%20recruiting%20new%20childcare%20workers%2C%20they%20do%20not%20consistently%20measure%20whether%20employee%20retention%20efforts%20are%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20military's%20childcare%20shortages%20aren't%20unique%20to%20the%20armed%20forces.%20Many%20Americans%20in%20the%20civilian%20world%20struggle%20to%20find%20reliable%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-too-expensive-unaffordable-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereasonably%20priced%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-paid-over-fifty-thousand-dollars-for-childcare-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyear%20of%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20amounts%20to%20an%20entire%20average%20salary%2C%20costing%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%20The%20cost%20of%20childcare%20in%20the%20US%20has%20increased%20by%20over%20150%25%20over%20the%20last%20quarter-century%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchart-expensive-daycare-childcare-inflation-working-parents-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econtinues%20to%20climb%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20often%20outpacing%20inflation.%20In%20some%20areas%2C%20childcare%20costs%20can%20exceed%20rent%20or%20mortgage%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-kids-are-still-waiting-for-childcare-spots-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771677241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998b84e2237a6a8f0cd8fe3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-kids-are-still-waiting-for-childcare-spots-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20military%20childcare%20waitlist%20affects%20thousands%20of%20families%2C%20highlighting%20gaps%20in%20support%20for%20working%20spouses%20and%20service%20members.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbaker%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-kids-are-still-waiting-for-childcare-spots-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%2026-year-old%20built%20a%20%24260%2C000%20ADU%20on%20her%20family's%20property.%20Now%2C%20she%20lives%20in%20the%20748-square-foot%20space%20with%20her%20sister.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20side-by-side%20of%20a%20woman%20in%20front%20of%20a%20house%20and%20a%20cozy%20sitting%20area%20in%20a%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69989845efb52c8bd0de9041%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMia%20Corippo%20renovated%20an%20ADU%20with%20her%20family.%3Cp%3EMia%20Corippo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMia%20Corippo%20and%20her%20family%20built%20a%20small%20home%20on%20her%20parents'%20land%20near%20Yosemite%20National%20Park.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECorippo%20then%20built%20an%20ADU%20for%20herself%20on%20the%20land%2C%20saving%20money%20and%20resources.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20%24260%2C000%20ADU%20is%20just%20over%20700%20square%20feet%20and%20has%20two%20bedrooms%20and%20bathrooms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Mia%20Corippo%20looks%20out%20of%20her%20door%20in%20the%20mornings%2C%20she's%20greeted%20by%20sweeping%20views%20of%20the%20Sierra%20Nevada%20Mountains%2C%20her%20rescue%20dog%20frolicking%20in%20her%20yard%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-of-4-downsized-house-to-save-money-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20small%20house%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20looks%20almost%20identical%20to%20hers%20just%20a%20few%20feet%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorippo%20doesn't%20live%20in%20a%20planned%20community%20with%20cookie-cutter%20homes%2C%20though.%20She%20lives%20in%20an%20accessory%20dwelling%20unit%2C%20or%20ADU%2C%20on%20her%20parents'%20land%2C%20sharing%20property%20and%20resources%20to%20save%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20one%20of%20thousands%20of%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-people-build-adus-housing-cost-benefits-cheaper-than-moving-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eturning%20to%20ADUs%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20more%20affordable%20alternative%20to%20traditional%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMia%20Corippo%20has%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20real%20estate%20and%20saving%20money%20from%20her%20parents%20over%20the%20years.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20stands%20with%20a%20coffee%20in%20front%20of%20a%20mountain%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F698f5553a645d11881894f3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223017%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMia%20Corippo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECorippo%2C%2026%2C%20grew%20up%20just%20outside%20Yosemite%20with%20her%20tight-knit%20family.%20The%20teacher%2C%20coach%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fmia_corippo%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtent%20creator%3C%2Fa%3E%20lived%20in%20Orange%20County%20for%20a%20few%20years%20for%20college%2C%20but%20she%20moved%20back%20in%20with%20her%20parents%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20parents%20have%20always%20been%20really%20big%20on%20us%20living%20with%20them%20and%20saving%20up%20money%20for%20as%20long%20as%20we%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20Corippo%20said%20of%20why%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-turned-garage-into-rent-free-apartment-for-son-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elived%20with%20her%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20her%20brother%20did%20the%20same.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20had%20the%20privilege%20of%20living%20with%20them%20when%20we%20came%20back%20from%20college%20and%20building%20our%20savings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorippo%20said%20her%20parents%20also%20instilled%20in%20her%20lessons%20about%20how%20real%20estate%20can%20set%20you%20up%20for%20financial%20success.%20When%20she%20was%20in%20high%20school%2C%20they%20turned%20a%20portion%20of%20their%20garage%20into%20an%20Airbnb.%20They%20let%20Corippo%20and%20her%20sister%20handle%20the%20housekeeping%20for%20the%20unit%20to%20help%20pay%20for%20their%20club%20volleyball%2C%20teaching%20her%20early%20that%20real%20estate%20could%20be%20a%20valuable%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIn%20late%202023%2C%20her%20family%20took%20those%20lessons%20and%20built%20a%20small%20home%20on%20property%20near%20Yosemite.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20in%20a%20camo%20hat%20smiles%20at%20something%20off%20to%20the%20right%20of%20the%20camera.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F698f7c30e1ba468a96ac0e05%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222225%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMia%20Corippo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECorippo's%20parents%20had%20purchased%20a%20small%20piece%20of%20land%20near%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyosemite-national-park-photos-government-shutdown-california-tourism-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enational%20park%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20California%20when%20real%20estate%20prices%20were%20low%2C%20unsure%20what%20to%20do%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20started%20toying%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20building%20a%20cabin%20on%20the%20land%2C%20Corippo%2C%20her%20brother%2C%20and%20her%20sister%20decided%20to%20pool%20their%20resources%20and%20invest%20in%20the%20build%20with%20her%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20were%20little%2C%20my%20parents%20invested%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-faces-ftc-scrutiny-apple-news-content-curation-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple%20stock%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20they%20bought%20for%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20Corippo%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20used%20those%20Apple%20stocks%20in%20our%20savings%20to%20invest%20in%20this%20first%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20650-square-foot%20house%20became%20a%20family%20project.%20It%20had%20one%20bedroom%2C%20a%20separate%20lofted%20sleeping%20area%2C%20and%20one%20bathroom.%20Corippo%20and%20her%20father%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20build%20cost%20around%20%24300%2C000%2C%20which%20included%20creating%20a%20well%2C%20septic%20tank%2C%20and%20driveway%20on%20the%20property.%20Corippo%20moved%20into%20the%20finished%20space%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20definitely%20a%20family%20collaboration%20of%20making%20it%20somewhere%20I%20could%20live%2C%20but%20also%20something%20that%20would%20be%20an%20investment%20once%20I%20moved%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Corippo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThen%2C%20Corippo%20decided%20she%20wanted%20a%20house%20for%20herself%20on%20their%20land.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20living%20area%20with%20a%20couch%2C%20a%20small%20closet%2C%20and%20a%20red%20door.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F698f7e7de1ba468a96ac0e8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMia%20Corippo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECorippo's%20family%20hoped%20to%20eventually%20rent%20out%20the%20primary%20residence%20on%20the%20property%2C%20so%20she%20knew%20she%20wouldn't%20live%20in%20it%20forever.%20She%20still%20had%20a%20decent%20amount%20of%20savings%20from%20living%20with%20her%20parents%20for%20a%20few%20years%2C%20giving%20her%20options%20for%20her%20next%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20still%20saved%20enough%20money%20to%20make%20something%20of%20my%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20Corippo%20said.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20crazy.%20I%20could%20probably%20make%20a%20small%20down%20payment%20on%20a%20really%20small%20house.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorippo%20could%20have%20bought%20her%20own%20place%2C%20but%20her%20dad%20had%20another%20idea%3A%20She%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-will-compensate-you-for-building-tiny-home-adu-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuild%20an%20accessory%20dwelling%20unit%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ADU)%2