mary%22%3A%22Instead%20of%20buying%20a%20new%20house%2C%20Mia%20Corippo%20used%20her%20savings%20to%20build%20a%20748-square-foot%20ADU%20on%20her%20parents'%20property%20in%20California.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sgrindell%40businessinsider.com%20(Samantha%20Grindell%20Pettyjohn)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-built-adu-on-family-land-california-yosemite-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20people%20want%20open%20relationships%2C%20but%20many%20don't%20last.%20A%20sex%20researcher%20shares%20the%203%20top%20reasons%20couples%20return%20to%20monogamy.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224992%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20holding%20hands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6994982fd3c7faef0ece6280%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENon-monogamy%20comes%20with%20its%20own%20challenges%2C%20Dr.%20Justin%20R.%20Garcia%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3Cp%3EHinterhaus%20Productions%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDr.%20Justin%20R.%20Garcia%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20said%20non-monogamy%20has%20gotten%20more%20popular.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20he%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopen-relationship-with-man-ten-years-older-2023-3%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopen%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20polyamory%20tend%20not%20to%20work%20for%20most%20people.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20find%20non-monogamy%20to%20be%20too%20much%20work%20in%20practice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpen%20relationships%20have%20gotten%20a%20cultural%20glow-up%20among%20younger%20adults.%20In%20practice%2C%20though%2C%20they're%20hard%20to%20pull%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20social%20media%20chatter%20where%20people%20in%20happy%20non-monogamous%20relationships%20report%20perks%20such%20as%20greater%20sexual%20satisfaction%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpolyamorous-wedding-commitment-ring-relationships-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%20deep%20partnerships%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20less%20restrictive%20love%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20outside%20the%20tweets%2C%20threads%2C%20and%20curated%20Instagram%20grids%2C%20the%20story%20is%20a%20bit%20more%20nuanced.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F09%2F14%2Fpublic-has-mixed-views-on-the-modern-american-family%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20Pew%20Research%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20Americans%20are%20divided%20on%20open%20marriages.%20Of%20about%205%2C000%20US%20adults%20surveyed%2C%2037%25%20found%20open%20marriages%20completely%20unacceptable.%20Younger%20generations%20approved%20more%20than%20anyone%20else%3A%20roughly%20half%20of%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%20were%20accepting%20of%20open%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Justin%20R.%20Garcia%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20has%20also%20witnessed%20the%20growing%20popularity%20of%20non-monogamy%20in%20his%20work.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20were%20talking%20about%20swinging%20in%20the%2060s%20and%2070s%2C%20but%20the%20language%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20attention%20to%20it%20changed%2C%20particularly%20over%20the%20last%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20citing%20Amy%20C.%20Moors%2C%20a%20sexuality%20scientist%20who%20noticed%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20people%20searching%20for%20terms%20related%20to%20polyamory%20between%202006%20and%202015.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20showing%20interest%20and%20actually%20engaging%20in%20the%20activity%20are%20two%20different%20things.%20In%20his%20new%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Intimate%20Animal%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F27096488%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20from%20his%20lab%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20research%20centers%20for%20human%20sexuality%20and%20relationships%2C%20found%20that%20one%20in%20five%20single%20adults%20in%20the%20US%2C%20out%20of%20about%208%2C700%20studied%2C%20have%20had%20some%20kind%20of%20consensual%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-partner-is-monogamous-but-im-not-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enon-monogamous%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20some%20point%20in%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hands%20holding%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699498c1e1ba468a96ac2a03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStudies%20suggest%20that%20more%20people%20have%20tried%20non-monogamy%20than%20maintained%20it%20long-term.%3Cp%3EVershinin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20looking%20at%20the%20past%20five%20years%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F319232548_Estimates_and_Correlates_of_Engagement_in_Consensually_Non-Monogamous_Relationships%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Garcia's%2C%20however%2C%20that%20number%20dropped%20significantly%2C%20suggesting%20that%20%26quot%3Bmore%20people%20try%20it%20than%20decide%20that%20it%20is%20a%20lifelong%20relationship%20structure%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20my%20social%20networks%2C%20that's%20been%20my%20experience%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20they%20never%20work%2C%20he%20added.%20According%20to%20multiple%20studies%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhile%20consensually%20open%20relationships%20might%20not%20work%20for%20everyone%2C%20or%20even%20for%20most%20people%2C%20there%20are%20many%20people%20for%20whom%20they%20do%20work%20perfectly%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20book.%20Those%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoly-vee-polyamorous-marriage-how-it-works-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehappy%20non-monogamous%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20don't%20fare%20psychologically%20or%20emotionally%20worse%20than%20content%20monogamous%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20who's%20a%20good%20candidate%20for%20it%3F%20My%20cheeky%20answer%2C%20but%20it's%20actually%20true%2C%20is%20those%20people%20who%20really%20want%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20similar%20to%20'What's%20the%20right%20amount%20of%20sex%20that%20we%20should%20be%20having%3F'%20It's%20as%20much%20as%20you%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20open%20relationships%20work%20for%20everyone.%20Based%20on%20his%20research%2C%20Garcia%20shared%20the%20most%20common%20reasons%20non-monogamous%20partnerships%20don't%20work%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225465bf7a-886f-4264-a456-afba5e0c8929%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20takes%20work%20to%20balance%20partners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224526%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20people%20hugging%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69949a82e1ba468a96ac2a50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223394%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDevoting%20enough%20time%20to%20your%20partners%20can%20be%20challenging.%3Cp%3EFG%20Trade%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjessica-fern-polysecure-book-consensual-nonmonogamy-polyamory-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20common%20challenges%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20non-monogamous%20partnerships%20might%20be%20our%20own%20biology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20such%20a%20fundamental%2C%20evolved%20drive%20to%20form%20intense%20pair%20bonds%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said%2C%20ones%20that%20biologists%20theorize%20helped%20us%20thrive%20as%20a%20species%20over%20time.%20In%20his%20book%2C%20he%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bour%20brains%20don't%20appear%20particularly%20well-suited%20to%20processing%20intimacy%20with%20more%20than%20one%20partner%20at%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20be%20it%20another%20romantic%20partner%20or%20a%20sexual%20fling.%20Even%20fantasies%20of%20threesomes%2C%20Garcia%20said%2C%20more%20often%20involve%20an%20existing%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20romance%20is%20most%20often%20defined%20by%20sustained%20attention%20and%20effort%2C%20then%20it%20becomes%20more%20difficult%20when%20one%20or%20both%20partners%20have%20other%20people%20to%20focus%20on.%20Introducing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopen-marriage-partner-moved-in-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20partner%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20shared%20home%20can%20cause%20friction%20with%20a%20spouse%2C%20as%20can%20skipping%20dinner%20with%20a%20spouse%20to%20spend%20it%20with%20another%20significant%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarcia%20said%20one%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bprevailing%20rationales%26quot%3B%20for%20consensual%20non-monogamy%20is%20having%20%26quot%3Btoo%20much%20love%20to%20give.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20the%20opposite%20is%20true%3A%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20don't%20have%20the%20biological%2C%20psychological%2C%20and%20social%20tools%20to%20love%20more%20than%20one%20person%20at%20a%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228dc57517-1bd9-413e-9a76-65ab6179f71c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EExtra%20communication%20can%20be%20a%20turn-off%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225336%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20holding%20hands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.co