%20had%20attempted%20to%20form%20a%20polycule%20once%20told%20me%2C%20'It%20didn't%20work%2C'%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20wrote.%20%26quot%3B'I%20just%20pissed%20off%20two%20women%20instead%20of%20one.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-open-relationship-dont-work-most-people-sex-researcher-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771676641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69949816a645d11881897254%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-open-relationship-dont-work-most-people-sex-researcher-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dr.%20Justin%20R.%20Garcia%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20found%20that%20consensual%20non-monogamy%20doesn't%20work%20for%20most%20people.%20Here's%20why.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpugachevsky%40businessinsider.com%20(Julia%20Pugachevsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-open-relationship-dont-work-most-people-sex-researcher-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hedge%20fund%20filings%20reveal%20which%20managers%20started%202026%20exposed%20to%20software%20stocks%20%E2%80%94%20and%20which%20one%20made%20a%20prescient%20bet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Greg%20Coffey's%20profile%20taken%20from%20the%20right%20side%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998932f2237a6a8f0cd8a97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGreg%20Coffey%20held%20a%20large%20bet%20against%20Oracle%20going%20into%202026.%3Cp%3EIan%20MacNicol%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESeveral%20smaller%20hedge%20funds%20were%20concentrated%20in%20software%20stocks%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERegulatory%20filings%20show%20former%20Viking%20PM%20Brennan%20Diaz's%20Fernbridge%20was%20a%20big%20holder%20of%20Salesforce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20Greg%20Coffey's%20Kirkoswald%20held%20a%20large%20bet%20against%20Oracle%20to%20start%20the%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20software%20sell-off%20hasn't%20been%20pretty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20fears%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20would%20make%20software%20businesses%20obsolete%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fai-disruption-stock-selloff-software-tech-real-estate-trucking-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estocks%20like%20Salesforce%2C%20Oracle%2C%20Workday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20more%20have%20shed%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20in%20market%20cap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWho%20in%20the%20%245.2%20trillion%20hedge%20fund%20industry%20has%20been%20stung%20by%20this%20sell-off%20isn't%20entirely%20clear.%20Still%2C%20a%20recent%20release%20of%20regulatory%20filings%20of%20funds'%20holdings%20reveals%20which%20managers%20were%20most%20exposed%20to%20the%20sector%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year.%20It's%20unclear%20if%20these%20funds%20sold%20their%20stakes%20before%20the%20sell-off%20began%20or%20have%20weathered%20the%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20manager%20who%20stands%20out%20is%20Brennan%20Diaz's%20Fernbridge%20Capital%2C%20a%20stockpicking%20fund%20with%20roughly%20%242%20billion%20in%20assets.%20The%20firm%20began%20the%20year%20with%20more%20than%2022%25%20of%20its%20portfolio%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalesforce-survey-employees-ai-impact-tasks-output-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ein%20Salesforce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20its%20largest%20position.%20Its%20second-largest%20bet%2C%20which%20made%20up%20nearly%2015%25%20of%20its%20portfolio%20at%20the%20start%20of%202026%2C%20was%20in%20Workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20stocks%20are%20down%20more%20than%2025%25%20to%20start%20the%20year%2C%20as%20of%20publication%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiaz%2C%20a%20former%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20Viking%20Global%2C%20started%20the%20fund%20in%202019%2C%20according%20to%20his%20LinkedIn%20profile%2C%20after%20a%20stint%20at%20Junto%20Capital%2C%20another%20fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-viking-global-is-top-hedge-fund-launch-training-ground-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estarted%20by%20a%20Viking%20alum.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContour%20Asset%20Management%2C%20run%20by%20David%20Meyer%2C%20a%20former%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20European%20multistrategy%20fund%20Brummer%20%26amp%3B%20Partners%2C%20started%20new%20positions%20in%20Salesforce%20and%20Workday%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202025%2C%20filings%20show.%20The%20manager's%20Salesforce%20bet%20was%20its%20third-largest%20holding%20at%202026's%20onset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20long-running%20activist%20fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalesforce-drafts-plans-to-increase-profits-leaked-document-shows-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EValueAct%20has%20Salesforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20its%20largest%20position%2C%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%2011%25%20of%20its%20portfolio%2C%20and%20added%20to%20its%20stake%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter.%20The%20manager%20has%20been%20invested%20in%20the%20stock%20for%20years%2C%20and%20its%20chief%20investment%20officer%2C%20Mason%20Morfit%2C%20is%20on%20Salesforce's%20board%20of%20directors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESean%20Ma%2C%20who%20ran%20Hong%20Kong-based%20Snow%20Lake%20Capital%20before%20relocating%20to%20California%2C%20started%20M37%20Management%20to%20invest%20in%20AI%20and%20infrastructure.%20His%20firm%20bought%20100%2C000%20shares%20of%20Oracle%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20making%20Larry%20Ellison's%20company%20Ma's%20second-largest%20holding%20at%20the%20start%20of%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20managers%20above%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20one%20fund%20was%20skeptical%20enough%20about%20Oracle%20coming%20into%20the%20year%20that%20it%20was%20willing%20to%20bet%20heavily%20against%20the%20tech%20giant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKirkoswald's%20Greg%20Coffey%2C%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsohn-coffey-elliott-einhorn-return-to-fundamentals-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWizard%20of%20Oz%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20macro%20prowess%2C%20bought%20put%20options%20on%20Oracle%20worth%20close%20to%20%24400%20million%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20filings%20show.%20Put%20options%20are%20contracts%20that%20allow%20an%20investor%20to%20sell%20shares%20of%20a%20company%20at%20a%20set%20price%20for%20a%20limited%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20use%20them%20to%20bet%20against%20stocks%20they%20expect%20to%20decline%20in%20price%20over%20the%20life%20of%20the%20contract%2C%20because%20the%20structure%20allows%20them%20to%20sell%20a%20stock%20for%20more%20than%20it%20is%20worth%2C%20generating%20a%20profit%20from%20the%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20from%20the%20filings%20how%20long%20Kirkoswald's%20options%20contracts%20were%20for%20or%20whether%20the%20firm%20has%20closed%20any%20positions.%20The%20firm%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-software-sell-off-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771676341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699893382237a6a8f0cd8a99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-software-sell-off-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Greg%20Coffey's%20Kirkoswald%20made%20a%20large%20bet%20against%20Oracle%20going%20into%202026%2C%20regulatory%20filings%20show.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bsaacks%40businessinsider.com%20(Bradley%20Saacks)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-software-sell-off-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%2039%20but%20just%20started%20contributing%20to%20a%20401(k)%20account.%20I%20have%20what%20I%20call%20'retirement%20planning%20paralysis.'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emily%20Achler%20selfie%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6995fe79e1ba468a96ac3cd1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20has%20always%20struggled%20to%20plan%20for%20retirement.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Emily%20Achler%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20my%2020s%20and%2030s%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20live%20in%20the%20present%20and%20ignored%20retirement%20planning.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%20that%20I'm%20about%20to%20turn%2040%2C%20I've%20started%20contributing%20to%20a%20401(k)%2C%20but%20I'm%20behind.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20still%20have%20to%20combine%20my%20past%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20but%20I'm%20fighting%20retirement%20planning%20paralysis.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%2039%2C%20and%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20haphazard%2C%20chaotic%2C%20and%20borderline%20nonexistent.%20I%20feel%20a%20lot%20of%20shame%20around%20this%20fact%20because%20I%20should%20know%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20job%20out%20of%20college%20was%20at%20PBS%2C%20where%20I%20opened%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Feverbank-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETIAA%20retirement%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2022.%20Somewhere%20in%20the%20intervening%2018%20years%2C%20the%20retirement%20accounts%20at%20PBS%20switched%20from%20TIAA%20to%20Fidelity.%20I%20now%20get%20notifications%20from%20both%2C%20and%20it's%20confusing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20PBS%2C%20I%20worked%20for%20a%20public%20relations%20agency%20that%20most%20certainly%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fsafe-harbor-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20absolutely%20didn't%20sign%20up%20for%20it.%20After%20that%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20Redbox%2C%20where%20I%20again%20didn't%20enroll%20in%20a%20retirement%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20a%20twisty-turny%20career%20path%2C%20including%20a%20pandemic-era%20six-year%20stint%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-founders-raising-millions-for-their-ai-startups-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estartup%20founder%3C%2Fa%3E%20developing%20a%20new%20tech%20product%20for%20book%20lovers.%20During%20that%20time%2C%20I%20worried%20about%20money%20every%20day%2C%20so%20I%20wasn't%20saving%20anything%20for%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20that%20leaves%20me%20with%20a%20string%20of%20sparse%2C%20underfunded%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20regrets%20about%20the%20past%2C%20and%20worries%20about%20the%20future.%20I'm%20deep%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20what%20I%20call%20%26quot%3Bretirement%20planning%20paralysis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202d6776c-76ad-4235-acc8-01bfc71f0792%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetirement%20wasn't%20on%20my%20radar%20for%20the%20bulk%20of%20my%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20shied%20away%20from%20retirement%20planning%20throughout%20my%20career%20for%20the%20same%20reason%20I%20didn't%20freeze%20my%20eggs%20or%20plan%20for%20any%20aspect%20of%20the%20future%3A%20Today%20is%20the%20only%20day%20that%20is%20promised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20tried%20to%20live%20in%20the%20present%20because%20it%20feels%20presumptuous%20to%20plan%20the%20future.%20And%20the%20future%20always%20felt%20very%20far%20away%2C%20so%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20put%20planning%20off%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20my%2020s%20and%2030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20with%2040%20looming%2C%20I%20still%20feel%20uncertain%20about%20the%20future%2C%20but%20I%20also%20see%20my%20past%20avoidant%20behaviors%20as%20ones%20riddled%20with%20excuses%20and%20justifications.%20I%20suddenly%20realized%3A%20Just%20because%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20things%20will%20turn%20out%20doesn't%20mean%20I%20can't%20plan%20for%20future%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ab41a16-8bfb-49cd-8b7c-ff71cf4bc2ff%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20finally%20started%20saving%20for%20retirement%2C%20but%20still%20paralyzed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20I'm%20working%20full%20time%20at%20a%20B2B%20PR%20agency%2C%20and%20I'm%20finally%20maxing%20out%20my%20401(k).%20I've%20now%20doubled%20my%20total%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-retirement-savings-wealth-ai-abundance-personal-finance-experts-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20my%20previous%2015%2B%20years%20of%20corporate%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20still%20have%20at%20least%20two%2C%20maybe%20three%2C%20different%20retirement%20accounts.%20I%20know%20I%20should%20combine%20them%20all%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20know%20where%20to%20start%20or%20the%20best%20way%20to%20go%20about%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20that%20401(k)s%20can%20be%20rolled%20over%20or%20rolled%20up%2C%20so%20I%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20get%20this%20ball%20rolling%2C%20but%20I'm%20still%20struggling%20to%20find%20the%20motivation.%20It%20feels%20like%20total%20planning%20paralysis.%20This%20is%20my%20next%20big%20hurdle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f195200c-9875-4e67-88fd-cd5811dc215c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20I%20feel%20about%20my%20future%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOptimistically%2C%20I%20would%20love%20to%20be%20in%20my%20late%2060s%20and%20retired.%20I%20want%20to%20travel%2C%20hike%2C%20and%20volunteer.%20I%20like%20to%20imagine%20that%20I'll%20relax%20by%20reading%20books%20in%20my%20little%20cozy%20nook%20of%20a%20cabin%20in%20the%20hills%20of%20a%20forest%20overlooking%20a%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20realistically%2C%20I%20see%20myself%20working%20into%20my%2070s%2C%20not%20by%20choice%20but%20necessity%20%E2%80%94%20joining%20the%20growing%20ranks%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-we-learned-from-americas-oldest-workers-80-over-80-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eolder%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20can't%20afford%20to%20stop.%20My%20current%20juncture%20makes%20me%20think%20of%20a%20famous%20Joni%20Mitchell%20line%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20got%20me%20hoping%20for%20the%20future%20and%20worrying%20about%20the%20past.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20do%20regret%20some%20of%20my%20past%20choices%2C%20but%20I'm%20addressing%20them%20now.%20Writing%20this%20essay%20is%20my%20first%20step%20out%20of%20paralysis.%20I'm%20also%20scheduling%20a%20meeting%20with%20a%20financial%20advisor%20next%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20I'm%20telling%20my%20friends%20about%20my%20retirement%20anxiety.%20I'm%20learning%20that%20admitting%20I'm%20overwhelmed%20doesn't%20make%20me%20a%20failure%3B%20it%20makes%20me%20honest.%20And%20being%20honest%20is%20a%20good%20first%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-age-just-started-retirement-planning-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771675621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6995fe83a645d11881898533%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-age-just-started-retirement-planning-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20I%20was%20younger%2C%20I%20didn't%20plan%20for%20the%20future%3B%20I%20ignored%20retirement%20planning.%20Now%20that%20I'm%20about%20to